It's a cute small outlet. We ordered a number of things like burger, pizza, vada pao, chicken roll.
Burger could have been better if it was warmer. The pizza was nice (not restaurant quality but better than the one you expect at such outlets.
The vada pao was good and the chicken roll was great with all the juicy pieces of chicken and their tasty sauce.

DLF has many jewels among itself in terms of small food outlets and this one can truly be regarded as one. One thing is for sure that this outlet can give many popular outlets a run for their money provided they make it big. 
Though being a small outlet, their burgers are really good and its a must try. 
We ordered the crispy chicken burger, to compare it with the one from Burger king, and its actually better with the lettuce providing the much needed base to the burger which lacks in the one from Burger King.
It's a little dearer that the popular food outlets but its criminal to miss this outlet. Head out here and enjoy some truly delicious burgers.

Have tried the veg wraps and burgers here. Got to give it to them for the awesome food. The wraps are heavenly. The burger patties and bun are out of the world. I only wish they topped it with some caramelised onions. The prices are also reasonable.
Only downside is the that the starters are bit oily. So it might not be a good idea to try those.

THE BEST BURGER I HAVE HAD IN MY LIFE!!! I have had the King's Special Non-veg Burger for three nights in a row and hell, I see this becoming an addiction!
The bun is always fresh, the chicken patty crisp, soft and cooked to the right extent, the condiments minimal so that nothing overpowers the taste of the patty and most importantly, the portions of onion, tomato and cabbage included are only enough to enhance the taste of the patty!
Anybody in the DLF area in Hyderabad needs to try this.

Ordered a tandoori chicken burger and a chicken mixed spicy rolls to cater to some midnight hunger pangs..
The burger had nothing tandoori about it and was spilling mayo all over (was looking for mint chutney) but this tasted more like McChicken and Chicken whopper had a malbutruoned baby.
The rolls were just like cigar sized chicken nuggets, nothing like the photos, and full of unnecessary veggies, bad after taste.
Delivery was on time but the guy made me walk a Km to find him, because he couldn't find me. 
Over all give it a skip from our end !
